div1.p:
In the District Court, holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of Jeremiah Mangan for a writ of Habeas Corpus Order
In making and filing the petition of Jeremiah Mangan, duly signed and verified by him, whereby in offense that he is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by one John H. McGraw Sheriff of King County, W. T., in the County Jail of said County, and stating where said illegally consists, from which in appears to me that a writ of Habeas Corpus aught to issue, it is ordered That a writ of Habeas Corpus issue and of and another The issue of The where entitled writ directed to the said John H. McGraw, commanding him to have the body of the said Jeremiah Mangan before me at the of said Court on the 27th day of May A. D. 1889 at 4 o'clock P. M., to do and retrieve what shall then and there be considered something the said Jeremiah Mangan together with the time and cause of his detention, and that he has then and there said writ Dated on the 25th day of May A. D. 1889 C. H. Hanford Judge

A-374 E 6867 T Application of J. Mangan for writ of Habeas Corpus Order
FILED MAY 27 1889 R M Hopkins Clerk. By H T Harmon Deputy Clerk.
